The paper deals with the construction and analysis of low-density codes, which are commonly used in information theory and coding theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of algorithms and optimization techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The analysis techniques used in the paper involve probabilistic methods and statistical learning, which could place it in cs.SI (Statistical Learning) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
